HOUSE BILL 1056
L2 5lr2980
By: Delegate Conaway
Introduced and read first time: February 5, 2025
Assigned to: Environment and Transportation and Ways and Means
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Local Government – Excise Tax on Plastic and Paper Carryout Bags
3 FOR the purpose of requiring a county to impose an excise tax on the amount of a fee
4 charged by a retailer to a customer for a plastic or paper carryout bag that exceeds
5 the amount required by local law; providing for the allocation of the excise tax
6 revenue between the county and the State; and generally relating to an excise tax on
7 certain fees for plastic and paper carryout bags.
8 BY adding to
9 Article – Local Government
10 Section 20–610
11 Annotated Code of Maryland
12 (2013 Volume and 2024 Supplement)
13 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
14 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
15 Article – Local Government
16 20–610.
17 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “RETAILER” MEANS A PERSON ENGAGED IN THE
18 RETAIL SALE OF GOODS.
19 (B) SUBJECT TO SUBSECTION (C) OF THIS SECTION, IF A COUNTY ENACTS A
20 LOCAL LAW THAT REQUIRES A RETAILER TO CHARGE AT THE POINT OF SALE A FEE
21 FOR PROVIDING A PLASTIC OR PAPER CARRYOUT BAG TO A CUSTOMER, THE COUNTY
22 SHALL IMPOSE AN EXCISE TAX ON ANY AMOUNT OF THE FEE THAT THE RETAILER
23 CHARGES THAT IS IN EXCESS OF THE MINIMUM AMOUNT REQUIRED BY THE LOCAL
24 LAW.
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
