2 HOUSE BILL 1056
1 (C) (1) THE AMOUNT OF THE EXCISE TAX IMPOSED BY THE COUNTY
2 SHALL BE ON EACH CENT THAT THE RETAILER CHARGES IN EXCESS OF THE
3 MINIMUM AMOUNT REQUIRED BY LOCAL LAW AS FOLLOWS:
4 (I) FOR THE COUNTY WHERE THE RETAILER IS LOCATED,
5 ONE–THIRD OF EACH CENT; AND
6 (II) FOR THE STATE, ONE–THIRD OF EACH CENT.
7 (2) THE COUNTY SHALL:
8 (I) RETAIN THE EXCISE TAX REVENUE COLLECTED UNDER
9 PARAGRAPH (1)(I) OF THIS SUBSECTION; AND
10 (II) REMIT THE EXCISE TAX REVENUE COLLECTED UNDER
11 PARAGRAPH (1)(II) OF THIS SUBSECTION TO THE COMPTROLLER TO BE CREDITED
12 TO THE GENERAL FUND OF THE STATE.
13 (3) THE RETAILER MAY RETAIN THE REMAINING ONE–THIRD OF EACH
14 CENT CHARGED IN EXCESS OF THE MINIMUM AMOUNT REQUIRED BY LOCAL LAW TO
15 COVER ADMINISTRATIVE COSTS FOR COLLECTING AND REMITTING THE TAX UNDER
16 THIS SECTION.
17 (D) A COUNTY SHALL ADMINISTER AND COLLECT THE TAX UNDER THIS
18 SECTION IN CONJUNCTION WITH THE FEE ON PLASTIC OR PAPER CARRYOUT BAGS
19 REQUIRED BY LOCAL LAW.
20 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
21 1, 2025.

